        title: 'Two Correct Rules, One Broken Outcome',
        html: '<p>Neither half of Vanish–Doom is a bug in isolation. Making an invisible target evade physical attacks but remain vulnerable to magic is a deliberate, internally consistent design. Likewise, granting magic a guaranteed hit against an invisible target is a reasonable rule. The defect is in the order of operations: the engine confirms the spell will hit before it consults the target\'s resistance to instant death.</p><p>Because immunity is checked too late, the death flag is applied to enemies the designers explicitly protected. The exploit is thus an emergent property of how the rules are sequenced rather than a single mistaken value — a reminder that the interactions between systems are as much a part of a game\'s behaviour as the systems themselves.</p>',
